'''''Çanakkale 1915''''' ({{lang-eng|Gallipoli 1915}}) is a 2012 Turkish historical [[drama film]] directed by [[Yesim Sezgin]] as [[Screenwriter|screen-written]]  by [[Turgut Özakman]] based upon his own 2008 novel ''Diriliş: Çanakkale 1915''.<ref name="Variety 1"/><ref name="Hürriyet Daily News 1">{{cite news|last1=Güler|first1=Emrah|title=Surge of films on Gallipoli Campaign - More films to come|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/surge-of-films-on-gallipoli-campaign.aspx?pageID=238&nID=31316&NewsCatID=381|accessdate=24 April 2015|work=[[Hürriyet Daily News]]|date=1 October 2012}}</ref><ref name=Sondakika>{{cite news|last1=staff|title=Azerbaycan'ın Kiev Büyükelçiliği'nde Çanakkale Resepsiyonu|url=http://www.sondakika.com/haber/haber-azerbaycan-in-kiev-buyukelciligi-nde-canakkale-7233705/|accessdate=25 April 2015|language=Turkish|publisher=Son Dakika|date=24 April 2014}}</ref>  Released theatrically on 1,000 screens across Turkey and Europe<ref name="Variety 1"/><ref name="Haber Turk"/><ref name="AnadoluJet Magazine">{{cite news|last1=Karahan|first1=Jülide|title=The Trick Is In Special Effects|url=http://www.anadolujet.com/aj-en/anadolujet-magazin/2012/october/articles/the-trick-is-in-special-effects.aspx|accessdate=1 May 2015|publisher=[[AnadoluJet|AnadoluJet Magazine]]|date=October 2012}}</ref> in October 2012, the film was never released commercially in the United States,<ref name="Indiana University">{{cite web|last1=staff|title=Çanakkale 1915|url=http://www.cinema.indiana.edu/?post_type=film&p=5824|publisher=[[Indiana University]]|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref> but premiered on [[ATV (Turkey)|ATV television]] on 17 March 2015.<ref name="Haberin Markasi">{{cite news|last1=staff|title=Çanakkale 1915 ATV izle 17/03/2015 Film iZLE|url=http://www.haberinmarkasi.com/yasam/canakkale-1915-atv-izle-17032015-film-izle-h265.html|accessdate=25 April 2015|language=Turkish|publisher=Haberin Markasi|date=17 March 2015}}</ref>

==Plot==
The story of the film is about the [[Gallipoli Campaign]] during [[World War I]] on the [[Gallipoli]] Peninsula in [[Turkey]] in 1915.  The film covers the resurrection of Turkey following its defeat in the [[Balkan War]], through depictions of Sergeant Mehmet Ali (Ali Ersan Duru) from [[Biga, Çanakkale|Biga]], Corporal Seyit and many others.  To help Russia and threaten Constantinople, the [[Allies of World War I|Allies]] try to force through the Dardanelles Straight with a large fleet. Through a series of historical sketches, the film documents how they were defeated despite many difficulties and hardships.

